        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-04-19T10:46:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-04-19T10:46:00-05:00" n="144"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <head>144. Telegram From the Commander in Chief, Atlantic (<persName
                        corresp="#p_DARL1" type="from">Dennison</persName>) to the Commander of
                    Special Task Group 81.8 (<persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1" type="to"
                        >Clark</persName>)<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d144fn0">Source: Naval
                        Historical Center, Area Files, Bumpy Road Materials. Top Secret; Operational
                        Immediate; Exclusive. Repeated to <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                        >JCS</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Norfolk</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-04-19T10:46:00-05:00">April 19, 1961, 10:46 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>191546Z. Bumpy Road. Exclusive for RAdm <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1"
                        >Clark</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_DARL1">Dennison</persName>,
                        <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GMGDW1">Gen Gray</persName>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>A.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_CTG1">CTG</gloss> 81.8 191448Z.<note n="1"
                            xml:id="d144fn1">In this telegram, sent to <persName corresp="#p_DARL1"
                                >Dennison</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_GMGDW1"
                                >Gray</persName> at 9:48 a.m., April 19, <persName
                                corresp="#p_CRAJE1">Clark</persName> reported a request to his Task
                            Group from the <gloss target="#t_CEF1">CEF</gloss> for close air support
                            to meet an attack led by tanks against the <gloss target="#t_CEF1"
                                >CEF</gloss> position on the beach. (Ibid.) <persName
                                corresp="#p_CRAJE1">Clark</persName> had reported 34 minutes earlier
                            that <gloss target="#t_CEF1">CEF</gloss> forces on Blue Beach were under
                            artillery fire. (<gloss target="#t_CTG1">CTG</gloss> 81.8 telegram
                            191414Z to CINC-LANTFLT, April 19; ibid.)</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>B.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 994247 <gloss target="#t_DTG1"
                            >DTG</gloss> 172035Z.<note n="2" xml:id="d144fn2">
                            <ref target="#d115">Document 115</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>C.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 994309 <gloss target="#t_DTG1"
                            >DTG</gloss> 181837Z.<note n="3" xml:id="d144fn3">
                            <ref target="#d122">Document 122</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>D.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 994369 <gloss target="#t_DTG1"
                            >DTG</gloss> 190838Z.<note n="4" xml:id="d144fn4">
                            <ref target="#d140">Document 140</ref>.</note>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Close air support cannot be furnished. Restrictions of ref B are
                                applicable. Only exceptions to 15 mile limitation so far authorized
                                are refs C and D.<note n="5" xml:id="d144fn5">At 10:33 a.m.,
                                        <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1">Clark</persName> reported to
                                        <persName corresp="#p_DARL1">Dennison</persName> that the
                                        <gloss target="#t_CEF1">CEF</gloss> commander had repeated
                                    his plea for close air support; the <gloss target="#t_CEF1"
                                        >CEF</gloss> was under continuing artillery fire and had
                                    been attacked twice by aircraft. (<gloss target="#t_CTG1"
                                        >CTG</gloss> 81.8 telegram 191533Z to <gloss
                                        target="#t_CINCLANTFLT1">CINCLANTFLT</gloss>, April 19;
                                    Naval Historical Center, Area Files, Bumpy Road Materials) At
                                    11:09 a.m., <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1">Clark</persName>
                                    suggested that he be authorized to take advantage of the fact
                                    that two hostile planes were circling near one of his destroyers
                                    in order to launch an air strike from the Essex. (<gloss
                                        target="#t_CTG1">CTG</gloss> 81.8 telegram 191609Z to <gloss
                                        target="#t_CINCLANTFLT1">CINCLANTFLT</gloss>, April 19;
                                    ibid.)</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
